what if we made our lives ones lived out abundance, rather than scarcity? do we have the faith to believe that there will be an abundance? a fear that has always hung on my heart is that of falling and failing too if we're being honest. the free fall of no control, and scavenging for scarcity is coming. then there finally comes a place: of letting go of all i can do and trusting that the lord will mind the gaps and do so with abundance. that's the hardest, but in this season of free falling before the landing it is a prayer for each hour to take it one step at a time. to back off the ledge of fear and let the lord shape this coming season. here's to an abundance in the face of fear and free falls. here's to a heart knowledge that there's infinitely more in store than what can be imagined.
